-- Bang & Olufsen Chairman Brian Petersen Leaves Over Strategy Disagreement
-- B y   C h r i s t i a n   W i e n b e r g
-- 2010-12-15T10:17:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-15/bang-olufsen-s-chairman-petersen-leaves-due-to-disagreement-on-strategy.html
Bang & Olufsen A/S , the maker of
luxury stereos and television sets, said Chairman  Brian Petersen  will leave his position after 11 weeks over
disagreements on the company’s strategy.  B&O fell for a  fifth day  in Copenhagen trading after the
Struer, Denmark-based company said Petersen will leave with
immediate effect, citing a “difference of opinion” with the
other board members.  Petersen was named chairman Sept. 27 when he replaced the
retiring  Joergen Worning .  Ole Andersen , chairman of the world’s
largest cleaning service provider, ISS A/S, will take over
Petersen’s position, B&O said today.  B&O shares fell as much as 2.5 percent and declined 0.5
kroner, or 0.8 percent, to 59.5 kroner at 11:11 a.m. local time.
The shares have lost 21 percent this year.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
